Congolese star Ferre Gola is set to jet into Kenya for a dual Easter performance in Nairobi and Mombasa. The 100 Kilos hitmaker will land on April 12 and have a meet-and-greet with fans in the afternoon at Meladen Restaurant.On Good Friday, Ferre will take the stage at KICC and on Easter Monday, he will fly to Mombasa for a concert at Mamba village. Currently, Ferr&eacute; Gola has three albums, including Sens Interdit (2007), Qui est derri&egrave;re toi (2009) and Bo&icirc;te noire. His musical repertoire consists of nearly 60 beautiful songs.